# deploy-test2.out - Card Shopper (improve pass, LOCAL)

Terminal-bound deploy-test that the first run could not perform. Verified against a
LOCAL preview only (python3 -m http.server 4178 over
michaelwegter.com/public/demos/card-shopper/). Never polled the live URL.

## Build
- `cd michaelwegter.com && npm install && npm run build` -> PASS (vite v6.4.2, 46
  modules, built in ~5s, no errors). Demo is static under public/, copied verbatim.

## Fix applied during this pass (root cause: demo would not load)
- The demo loaded React/react-dom/htm from `unpkg.com`, which is BLOCKED (403) by
  this environment (Zscaler). First paint threw `React is not defined` /
  `htm is not defined` and rendered nothing.
- Vendored the three UMD libs locally into
  `public/demos/card-shopper/assets/vendor/` (react@18, react-dom@18, htm@3,
  sourced from jsdelivr) and pointed `index.html` at the local copies. The demo is
  now truly self-contained with zero CDN dependency, which also protects real users
  from any future unpkg outage. No app logic changed.

## Playwright results (22/22 PASS, headless chromium, localhost:4178)
- first paint: root rendered, NO console errors, NO page errors.
- hero value-box flip: pin -> shop -> face-down flipcard click reveals the card
  face (`.reveal-actions`).
- make-offer 85% threshold: offer of 469 (>= 85% of asking) -> `.status-accepted`;
  offer of 1 (< 85%) -> `.status-declined`. Matches `amount >= price*0.85` in app.js.
- AI upload accept/override: subscription activated via mock Stripe -> AI-detect
  reaches the editable review -> Override unlocks the price field -> Accept re-locks
  to the suggested market price -> Publish shows "Listing published".
- localStorage persistence: `cardshopper:v1` written and survives a full reload.
- no console errors across the entire run.

Script: `upwork-runs/card-shopper/deploy-test.mjs` (re-runnable;
`BASE_URL` env overrides the target, defaults to http://localhost:4178/).

## handoff
- produced: deploy-test2.out (VERDICT pass) + deploy-test.mjs.
- changed: index.html now loads vendored React/react-dom/htm from
  `assets/vendor/` instead of unpkg (unpkg is 403 here); added 3 vendor files.
- verified: clean build, 22/22 Playwright checks, no console errors, all four hero
  flows + persistence exercised on localhost.
- next needs: media-capture grabs hero stills + recording and the 16:9 card png;
  registry screenshot flips from null; proposal embeds the stills. deploy must push
  the new vendor/ files + index.html change too.
- risks: none open locally; live verification not possible from this environment.

VERDICT: pass
